%S A272004 3,7,4,1,5,0,6,9,1
%N A272004 Decimal expansion of Cp(3), the molar specific heat of an triatomic ideal gas at constant pressure, in J mol^-1 K^-1.
%C A272004 Also the decimal expansion of Cv(4), the molar specific heat of a tetraatomic gas at constant volume.
%C A272004 The molar specific heat of an n-atomic gas at constant pressure and volume can be calculated respectively with the following formulae:
%C A272004 - Cv(n) = (n + 1/2) R;
%C A272004 - Cp(n) = (n + 3/2) R;
%C A272004 Where R = Cp(n) - Cv(n) = Cp(n) - Cp(n-1) = A081822 is IUPAC's value of the gas constant.
%H A272004 Kshitij Education, <a href="http://www.kshitij-iitjee.com/molar-specific-heat-of-an-ideal-gas">Molar specific heat</a>
%H A272004 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heat_capacity">Heat capacity </a>
%F A272004 Cp(3) = (3 + 3/2) * R = 9/2 * A081822.
%F A272004 Cp(3) = Cp(2) + R = Cv(3) + R = A272003 + A081822.
%e A272004 Cp(3) = 37.4150691 J mol^-1 K^-1.
